					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2340829#post-4029100</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2340829/scp-3799#post-4029100</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 19 Oct 2018 15:32:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>AntagonistChan</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2151601</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Man, I was really on the fence about this until the very last log. -1's attitude towards the snow- that it's super pretentious- just felt really fresh and awesome and interesting to me. Because, like, that's exactly how I felt reading the third document- that it was a ton of pretentious, Thanos-esque bullshit. And the fact that the characters in-universe feel the same way as me made me officially decide that, yeah, I like this one.<br /> Keep in mind, I like the rest of it, too. I was just on the fence because I'm kinda tired of the &quot;this anomaly is proof that something terrible happened in an alternate timeline&quot; SCP trope in general. But, this is a very good use of that trope, so.<br /> Though, now that I think about it, it's kinda sad. -1's final request was to &quot;remember us,&quot; but the documents are restricted to the O5 and people they authorize.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
